RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 66. Maiden Claiming Purse 13000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WARRIOR'S STAR moved forward under mild coaxing to take command and set the pace inside on or just off the rail, continued on a clear advantage up the backstretch, extended the margin when asked coming to the five-sixteenths, came out a bit turning into upper stretch and fought on to hold. BIG PETE stalked two to three wide, was between runners late up the backstretch and on the far turn, put to urging at the five-sixteenths, lugged in just a bit nearing the eighth pole then immediately switched outside the leader, closed the gap but was only second best. CURIOUS IRISH bobbled just slightly at the start, moved forward inside then rated in behind the leader racing just off the rail, saved ground inside foes on the far turn, put to a drive coming past the quarter pole, was in just a hair tight near the furlong marker and ran on. FOOL'S MIRAGE stalked three to four wide, raced outside foes into and on the far turn and was asked for more at the five-sixteenths, could only run on evenly. SHINE JACK'S DREAM was caught four to five wide early and was outrun.

ENTRY.NAME: Curious Irish
ENTRY.COMMENT: very slight bobble brk, rated insd-2p, bit tight 1/8, ran on

ENTRY.NAME: Warrior's Star
ENTRY.COMMENT: pace, inside-2/3path, urged 5/16, widened, lasted

ENTRY.NAME: Big Pete
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2-3w, lug in bit & switched out 1/8, closed gap, 2nd best

ENTRY.NAME: Fool's Mirage
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked, 3-4wide, ask 5/16, evenly

ENTRY.NAME: Shine Jack's Dream
ENTRY.COMMENT: 4-5w early, outrun

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 2 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 50. Maiden Claiming Purse 13000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FREYAS CATZ switched off the inside heading into the turn, went three wide on that bend in pursuit of the dueling leaders, struck the lead near the furlong grounds, drew clear and held safe. OKIE HOPE pursued three to four wide, was second best. PASCALA dueled inside a rival till the top of the stretch, came off the rail turning for home while putting that sparring partner away and with the lead, lacked the needed late kick. BROOKE'S ALL IN was devoid of early speed, raced four to five wide on the turn trailing the field and coming into upper stretch wider still, ran on to improve. AZUSA STREET shifted in leaving the backstretch, advanced inside on the turn reaching striking distance turning for home but lacked the needed late kick. RUNNIN BOOTS dueled outside, gave way. DUE TO TIMER MALFUNCTION RACE WAS HAND-TIMED.

ENTRY.COMMENT: switched out, 3w turn, led 1/8, drew clear, held safe

ENTRY.COMMENT: shifted in 7/16, saved ground, no kick

ENTRY.NAME: Okie Hope
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3-4w pursuit, second best

ENTRY.COMMENT: dueled, inside, off rail & led upper, no kick

ENTRY.NAME: Brooke's All In
ENTRY.COMMENT: no speed, 4-5w turn, ran on

ENTRY.NAME: Runnin Boots
ENTRY.COMMENT: dueled outside, gave way

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 3 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 91. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: INCA EMPIRE settled outside off the pace four wide, advanced three deep on the far turn making a bid at the five-sixteenths, was in command and drawing away by upper stretch and was geared down late. BIG SKIPPER dictated the pace racing on or just off the rail without much effort or pressure, faced increasing pressure heading to the far turn, was challenged midway on that bend and overtaken, proved no match for the winner but clearly second best. GHOST STRATEGY stalked the early pace then took closer order to apply moderate pressure heading to the far turn, had no late bid when asked. MR OKLAHOMA CITY tracked from inside, came out for the stretch run and failed to rally.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 4 1M Dirt CR: 79. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since February 8 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000, if for $7,500, allowed 3 lbs. (Maiden And Claiming Races For $5,000 Or Less Not Con sidered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: EUTYCHIA settled in behind the leader to track, advanced up the rail to take the lead at the half, was overtaken leaving the far turn but dug in through the stretch to regain command seventy yards from home and prevail. KIMBELL'S STRATEGY settled at the rear, switched off the inside and made a swift advance outside foes four wide on the far turn taking the lead at the quarter pole, appeared in command in upper stretch but was engaged by the inside rival dueling with that one before being outfinished. MISS M J stalked the pace then applied pressure from outside three deep midway up the backstretch, lacked the needed late kick. ROSE OF EKITA raced off the leaders while several paths removed from the inside early, moved nearer the rail heading to the far turn, appeared to steady just slightly about the three-eighths, failed to rally. SEE WHAT'S WHAT moved forward to set the pace two deep, faced mild pressure from outside then pressure from rivals both inside and outside, steadily weakened while switching out and had nothing left for the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Will Rogers S. WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 5 1M Dirt CR: 90. Stakes Purse 55000. FOR ACCREDITED OKLAHOMA-BREDS, THREE YEARS OLD. Nominations closed Thursday, April 27, 2023 with twenty (20). No nomination fee. $500 to pass the entry box. Starters to pay an additional $250 with $55,000 guaranteed. $50,000 of the $55,000 guaranteed mone y to be divided 60% to the winner, 20% to second, 11% to third, 6% to fourth and 3% to fifth. Oklahoma-Bred money to be divided 60% to the winner, 20% to second, 11% to third, 6% to fourth, and 3% to fifth. Weight, 122 lbs. Starters to be named through th e entry box by usual time of entry. This race will be limited to 10 starters. In the event the race overfills, highest earnings in 2022-23 shall be preferred. There will be no also-eligibles. A suitable award will be presented to the winning owner. A cust om saddle towel will be ordered for and given to each entrant.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GHOST HERO exchanged a light bump at the start, attended the pace from outside three to four wide, ramped up the pressure past the half dueling through the turn, took command in upper stretch and forged clear under vigorous hand urging. ROWDY RIVER pressed the pace two to three wide from between runners, dueled inside the winner but off the fence through the far turn, was no match for that one but second best. SEND THE BOSS exchanged a light bump at the start, stalked three to four wide and in the clear but could only go on one-paced. RACHEL'S CAPER set a pressured pace inside on or just off the rail, weakened past the half. DOMINANT OKIE rated off the pace inside early, saved ground both turns, failed to rally. CIMARRON SAND failed to threaten while racing off the inside part of the track.

ENTRY.COMMENT: rated inside early, no rally

ENTRY.COMMENT: pressured pace inside-2path, weakened past 1/2

ENTRY.NAME: Rowdy River
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed 2-3w btw, duel far turn, no match, 2nd best

ENTRY.NAME: Cimarron Sand
ENTRY.OWNER: Schroder Eugene Porter Larry C and Bullock Caleb
ENTRY.COMMENT: off inside, no threat

ENTRY.NAME: Ghost Hero
ENTRY.COMMENT: light bump brk, attended 3-4w, duel, forged clear

ENTRY.NAME: Send the Boss
ENTRY.COMMENT: light bump brk, stalked 3-4wide, evenly

RACE.FOOTNOTES: ELDON'S SAMURAI chased the pacesetter going two to three wide on the turn, struck the lead outside the furlong marker, moved clear and was geared down in the final stages. STREETSTER broke a step slowly then moved from between runners to pursue just off the pace going three to four wide on the turn, drifted about six deep into upper stretch, kicked on but was only second best. JEANO raced near the rail well back of the leaders, angled six deep turning for home and failed to menace. GOSPEL DANDY reared at the start, raced off the inside at the back and was not a factor.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: HANNAH FO FANNAH got away alertly but was allowed to settle off the leaders, went five wide on the turn, rallied outside in the drive and just got up. SECRET PASS set a pressured pace racing two wide with foes inside and out, was headed in upper stretch, fought back to retake the lead but was caught at the wire. AUNT LOTTIE steadied sharply at the start, moved forward in behind runners keen to go on but running up on heels, angled five wide coming to the top of the stretch, finished strongly making a late bid between runners that just fell short. RACE.FOOTNOTES: TOM'S GIRL settled off the pace inside, advanced near the rail then just off it on the far turn, shifted nearer the rail in mid-stretch, bid inside past the sixteenth and edged clear. DOUDOUDOUWANADANCE had light bumps on both sides at the start then moved forward and clear to set the pace racing well off the inside into the first turn going in the three path, moved in a bit and dictated terms two to three deep thereafter, faced inside pressure coming to the half, was clear again on the far turn, drifted in and out just a bit in late stretch and was outfinished. RED RIVER WITCH was bumped into a rival at the start, raced a bit rank early steadying slightly at the seven-eighths and three-quarter poles, was guided outside at that point, advanced outside heading to the far turn then reached striking distance three to four deep on that bend, ran on. EXPENSIVE LIAISON shifted in to the three path early on the first turn settling toward the rear, was still well back two to three wide on the far turn but improved position in the lane. IM THE BIGGER BEAR angled in past the seven-eighths and moved forward inside to press the pace by the three-quarter pole, came up empty in the stretch.
